---
title: Warm Grain Salad with Barley, Avocado & Burst Tomatoes
description: We love a good grain salad - it's all about the mix-ins! Here, we're tossing in creamy butter beans, silky avocado, and burst grape tomatoes for a fun mix of colors and textures. Torn basil adds a touch of lemony freshness for the perfect finish.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/54f5db476ced6e1c358b4569.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/54f5db476ced6e1c358b4569.pdf
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Mediterranean
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/warm-grain-salad-54f5db476ced6e1c358b4569
nutrition:
  calories: 753 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  carbohydrates: 117 g
  protein: 24 g
  fiber: 31 g
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
---

Place @pearl barley{3/4%cup} in a large #pot with 4 cups of @water{4%cups}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, reduce to a simmer, and cook for about ~{20%minutes}, until tender. Drain and set aside.

Meanwhile, halve the @grape tomatoes{1%bunch}. Tear the @basil{1%bunch}(torn). Drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%can}. Thinly slice the @shallot{1}(thinly sliced).

Heat @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} in a small #pan over medium heat. Add the tomatoes and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, tossing, for about ~{5%minutes}, until slightly softened. Set aside.

Meanwhile halve, and pit the @avocado{1}. Scoop out the flesh with a spoon and thinly slice.

> HINT: You can slice the avocado halves in the skin with a paring knife and use a spoon to scoop out the slices!

In a medium #bowl, whisk together @dijon mustard{1/2%tablespoon} (or more to taste), @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoons}, and @olive oil{1 1/2%tablespoons}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss in warm barley, avocado, butter beans, shallot, and tomatoes. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Serve the warm salad with torn basil on top!